[Gemini]: The `from_unix_seconds` function at line 75 contains a potential infinite loop. If the `seconds` parameter is `float('inf')`, the condition `abs(seconds) > MS_WATERSHED` will always be true, as infinity is greater than any finite number. Inside the loop, `seconds /= 1000` is executed, but `inf / 1000` results in `inf`, so the loop never terminates. This can be triggered if a function calling `from_unix_seconds` passes an infinite float value, leading to a Denial of Service (DoS) by consuming 100% of a CPU core.

The `get_numeric` function at line 64 can produce this `inf` value, as `float('inf')` is valid Python and will return `float('inf')`.

